column5: [Here's some info about what APIs are and how to use them] (https://westus.dev.cognitive.microsoft.com/docs/services/5a93fcf85b4ccd136866eb37/operations/5ac266295b4ccd1554da75ff).

To make sure that your App Service is online, follow these steps: 

1.  Go to the [Azure portal](https://portal.azure.com/). 

2. Select App Services, choose the App Service you want to check on, and then select the Overview section. 

3.  Copy the URL from the top of the page. 

4. Paste the URL into a new tab in your browser. You should get a message saying that the service is up and running. If your App Service is down, check out our [troubleshooting tips](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cognitive-services/qnamaker/how-to/troubleshooting-runtime) to find out how to restart it.
